@startuml
actor Student
    participant "React Frontend" as React
    participant AuthMiddleware
    participant RBACMiddleware
    participant MerchandiseController

    note over Student,MerchandiseController:  Scenario A: Student attempts club-admin-only action

    Student->React: Attempt to POST a new merchandise listing
    React->AuthMiddleware: POST /api/merchandise (with student JWT)
    AuthMiddleware->AuthMiddleware: Verify JWT signature → valid
    AuthMiddleware->AuthMiddleware: Decode token → role = "student"
    AuthMiddleware->RBACMiddleware: Pass to RBAC check
    RBACMiddleware->RBACMiddleware: Required role = "club_admin", actual = "student"
    RBACMiddleware-->React: 403 Forbidden {"message": "Access denied"}
    React-->Student: Error: You do not have permission

    note over Student,MerchandiseController:  Scenario B: Unauthenticated request

    Student->React: GET /api/orders/my (no token)
    React->AuthMiddleware: GET /api/orders/my (no Authorization header)
    AuthMiddleware->AuthMiddleware: No token found
    AuthMiddleware-->React: 401 Unauthorized {"message": "No token provided"}
    React-->Student: Redirect to login page

    note over Student,MerchandiseController:  Scenario C: Club admin accesses own resource

    actor ClubAdmin
    ClubAdmin->React: POST /api/merchandise (with club_admin JWT)
    React->AuthMiddleware: POST /api/merchandise (valid club_admin token)
    AuthMiddleware->AuthMiddleware: Verify + decode → role = "club_admin"
    AuthMiddleware->RBACMiddleware: Pass to RBAC check
    RBACMiddleware->RBACMiddleware: Required role = "club_admin" ✓
    RBACMiddleware->MerchandiseController: Next()
    MerchandiseController-->React: 201 Created

@enduml
